# StoneCore — Handcrafted Zen Decor

## Project Overview
StoneCore is an e-commerce website for handcrafted Zen decor products including stone gardens, miniature shrines, bonsai arrangements, and meditation accessories. The website features a dynamic product catalog powered by PHP and MySQL.

## Folder Structure
stonecore/
├── config.php ← Database connection
├── database.sql ← Import in phpMyAdmin
├── api/
│ ├── products.php ← GET all products
│ └── product.php ← GET single product
├── css/
│ ├── styles.css ← Main stylesheet
│ └── product-detail.css ← Product page styles
├── js/
│ ├── main.js ← Homepage script
│ └── product-detail.js ← Product page script
├── Product/ ← Product images folder
├── img/ ← Other images folder
├── checkout.html ← Checkout page
├── product-detail.html ← Product detail page
└── index.html ← Main website

text

## Prerequisites
- XAMPP / WAMP / MAMP (PHP 7.4+ and MySQL)
- Web browser (Chrome/Firefox recommended)

## Step 1 — Database Setup
1. Start XAMPP and turn on **Apache** and **MySQL** services
2. Open phpMyAdmin: `http://localhost/phpmyadmin`
3. Click on **New** database
4. Database name: `stonecore_db` → Click **Create**
5. Click **Import** tab
6. Choose the `database.sql` file from the `DataBase` folder
7. Click **Go** at the bottom
8. Sample products will be inserted automatically

## Step 2 — Config Update
Open `config.php` and update your database credentials:

```php
<?php
// config.php — Database Connection

define('DB_HOST', 'localhost');
define('DB_USER', 'root');           // Change if your username is different
define('DB_PASS', '');               // Add your MySQL password if any
define('DB_NAME', 'stonecore_db');

$conn = new mysqli(DB_HOST, DB_USER, DB_PASS, DB_NAME);

if ($conn->connect_error) {
    die(json_encode([
        'success' => false,
        'message' => 'Connection failed: ' . $conn->connect_error
    ]));
}

$conn->set_charset('utf8mb4');
?>
Step 3 — Project Location
Move the entire stonecore folder to your web server directory:

Server	Path
XAMPP	C:/xampp/htdocs/stonecore/
WAMP	C:/wamp/www/stonecore/
MAMP	/Applications/MAMP/htdocs/stonecore/
Step 4 — View Website
Open your browser and go to:

text
http://localhost/stonecore/
API Endpoints
Method	URL	Description
GET	http://localhost/stonecore/api/products.php	Get all products
GET	http://localhost/stonecore/api/product.php?id=1	Get single product
API Response Examples
GET /api/products.php
json
{
  "success": true,
  "products": [
    {
      "id": 1,
      "name": "Handcrafted Miniature Zen Garden Diorama",
      "category": "Zen Stack",
      "price": 1899,
      "description": "Handcrafted stacked river stones...",
      "image": "Product/.../image.png"
    }
  ]
}
GET /api/product.php?id=1
json
{
  "success": true,
  "product": {
    "id": 1,
    "name": "Handcrafted Miniature Zen Garden Diorama",
    "category": "Zen Stack",
    "price": 1899,
    "original_price": 2499,
    "rating": 4.8,
    "reviews": 127,
    "description": "...",
    "features": ["..."],
    "details": {...},
    "images": ["..."],
    "in_stock": true
  }
}
Workflow
User visits Homepage → Sees all products

Clicks on a product → Opens product detail page

Clicks Buy Now → Goes to checkout page

Fills shipping details → Places order

Order is logged (console) and success message shown

Troubleshooting
Database Connection Error
Make sure MySQL is running in XAMPP

Check username/password in config.php

Verify database name stonecore_db exists

Products Not Loading on Website
Check browser console for errors (F12 → Console tab)

Make sure api/products.php returns JSON data

Verify js/main.js path is correct

404 Errors
Make sure project is inside htdocs folder

URL should be http://localhost/stonecore/ not file:///...

Check that index.html exists in the folder

